Sentencas: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite showed superior kinetics for the electro-reduction of oxygen.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The generic formulation was La1-xSrxCu1-yFeyO3 (LSCuF) where x ranged from 0.2 to 0.3 and y varied from 0 to 0.4.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Doping with copper improved the electrocatalytic activity compared with undoped material.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In oxygen, the La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3 sample showed current densities approximately 2-3 times that of La0.7Sr0.3FeO3 and 10 times that of La0.8Sr0.2FeO3.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This improvement was confirmed with cyclic voltammetric studies on half cells and on full fuel cell tests.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Copper doped materials have unusual electrochemical characteristics and copper apparently undergoes a one electron reduction at overpotentials less than -0.1 V.
Titulo: Copper doped lanthanum strontium ferrite for reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells
